description:
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;St Raphael&#39;s Hospice (SRH), has been well established in Merton and Sutton for many years, It is now entering a new, exciting phase, becoming an independent stand-alone charity, in the next few months. We are working to deliver a high quality patient focused service, within our resources and capacity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Hospice provides a range of specialist palliative care services to a population of just over 400,000. A dedicated staff of 135 (plus around 40 bank staff) is supported by over 800 volunteers, based at the Hospice site, our fund-raising office and our 11 retail sites around the boroughs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to add to our team in order to enhance our responsive and flexible service delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We areseeking to recruit experienced Band 5 Staff Nurses to join our bank.You must bean enthusiastic and committed registered nurse who isflexible with good communication skills and has the ability to work at least 2 bank shifts per month.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A supportive multi-disciplinary team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free on-site parking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities for training and development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discount in all of our shops and Orangery Café&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assess to the Employee Assistance Programme (EAP)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staff pilates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clinical supervision with external facilitator&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Should you require any additional information or would like to come along for an informal visit please contact the HR team who will arrange for you on 0208 099 8679.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
